{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900728588,"sessionID":"ses_284132a8cffe0HAiP88L7LVkAl","part":{"id":"prt_d7bece383001xRfkORoy29R9aY","messageID":"msg_d7becd6910012p8WB7QQhjtiTP","sessionID":"ses_284132a8cffe0HAiP88L7LVkAl","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_cd68ec1dadde455bba8e2a82","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (directories, key files)\n2. Existing documentation (especially in docs/ directory)\n3. Any existing architecture or API documentation\n4. The project's tech stack and main components\n5. Any existing task tracking or planning files\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of the project structure, tech stack, existing docs, and any patterns used for documentation.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2841310e9ffejxxkSlMRvtRt1d (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a thorough understanding of the entire project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: AgentCube (SDD-TEE Benchmark)\n\n### 1. Project Identity\n\nThis repository at `/home/dsj/benchmark` is **not** the AgentCube source code itself -- it is an **SDD-TEE (Specification-Driven Development Token Efficiency Evaluation) benchmark framework** that uses the real open-source project [agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) as its evaluation subject. The benchmark measures token consumption, cost, and code quality across different AI coding tools and models when building the AgentCube project through a specification-driven workflow.\n\n### 2. Overall Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/\n├── .git/                          # Git repository\n├── .gitignore\n├── .pytest_cache/                 # Python test cache\n├── Makefile                       # Unified entry point for all benchmark operations\n├── README.md                      # Project overview (Chinese)\n├── PROPOSAL.md                    # Evaluation system design document (Chinese)\n├── PLAN.md                        # Implementation plan for AR-023 through AR-033 (1441 lines)\n├── proposal.md                    # Per-AR proposal (currently AR-032 Dockerfile spec)\n├── task.md                        # Original task description (Chinese)\n├── tasks.md                       # Task breakdown for AR-033 Python SDK\n├── requirements.txt               # Python dependencies (pyyaml, litellm, matplotlib, rich)\n├── configs/\n│   ├── config.yaml                # Benchmark configuration (tools, models, metrics, stages)\n│   └── litellm_config.yaml        # LiteLLM Proxy routing config\n├── specs/                         # 43 AR specification files (reverse-engineered from agentcube)\n│   ├── project.md                 # OpenSpec project context\n│   ├── test_spec.md               # Test specification\n│   ├── sandbox-orchestration/     # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── session-routing/           # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── code-execution/            # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── session-store/             # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── idle-cleanup/              # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── cli-toolkit/               # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── python-sdk/                # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── deployment/                # spec.md + design.md + client-go.md\n│   ├── ci-cd/                     # spec.md + design.md\n│   ├── integrations/              # spec.md + design.md\n│   └── testing/                   # agentcube_tdd_manifest.md\n├── scripts/                       # Benchmark engine and tooling\n│   ├── engine.py                  # Main benchmark driver (v5.1)\n│   ├── auditor.py                 # LiteLLM JSONL token auditor\n│   ├── schema.py                  # Data schema validation\n│   ├── report.py                  # HTML report generation\n│   ├── compare.py                 # Cross-run comparison\n│   ├── export.py                  # CSV/JSON/Markdown export\n│   ├── preflight.py               # Environment validation\n│   ├── validate.py                # Validation utilities\n│   ├── equivalence.py             # Code equivalence checking\n│   ├── aggregate.py               # Data aggregation\n│   ├── run_benchmark.sh           # Single benchmark entry\n│   ├── batch_benchmark.sh         # Batch benchmark entry\n│   └── adapters/                  # CLI tool adapters\n│       ├── base.py                # StageRecord + BaseAdapter\n│       ├── claude_code.py         # Claude Code adapter\n│       ├── gemini_cli.py          # Gemini CLI adapter\n│       ├── cursor_cli.py          # Cursor CLI adapter\n│       └── opencode_cli.py        # OpenCode CLI adapter\n├── sdk-python/                    # AgentCube Python SDK (partial implementation)\n│   ├── pyproject.toml             # Package metadata (agentcube-sdk v0.1.0)\n│   ├── agentcube/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py            # Exports CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter.py    # High-level Code Interpreter client\n│   │   ├── agent_runtime.py       # High-level Agent Runtime client\n│   │   ├── clients/\n│   │   │   ├── control_plane.py   # Workload Manager HTTP client\n│   │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # Router data plane client\n│   │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # Agent runtime data plane client\n│   │   └── utils/                 # HTTP, logging, general utilities\n│   └── tests/                     # SDK unit tests\n├── manifests/\n│   └── rbac/                      # Kubernetes RBAC manifests\n│       ├── rbac-all.yaml\n│       ├── namespace.yaml\n│       ├── kustomization.yaml\n│       ├── roles/, rolebindings/, clusterroles/, serviceaccounts/\n│       └── tests/\n├── docs/                          # Docusaurus documentation site\n│   ├── docusaurus.config.js       # Docusaurus configuration\n│   ├── sidebars.js                # Sidebar structure (7 sections)\n│   ├── package.json               # NPM dependencies\n│   └── docs/\n│       ├── introduction/          # index.md, quickstart.md, concepts.md\n│       └── architecture/          # overview.md, modules.md, data-flow.md, security.md, observability.md\n├── changes/                       # OpenSpec change directories (AR-026, AR-035, AR-037)\n│   └── AR-026/tasks.md            # CLI provider tasks (23 tasks, 6 phases)\n├── tasks/\n│   └── ar-030-tasks.md            # Helm chart tasks (34 tasks, 8 phases)\n├── workspaces/                    # Per-run isolated code workspaces\n│   └── v5.1/                      # Contains workspace from claude-code run\n├── results/                       # Benchmark results\n│   ├── runs/v5.1/                 # _full.json files + log backups\n│   └── reports/v5.1/              # HTML reports and comparison dashboards\n└── configs/\n    └── config.yaml                # Benchmark configuration\n```\n\n### 3. Tech Stack\n\n**Benchmark Framework (this repo):**\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language | Python 3.9+ |\n| CLI Framework | Typer, Click |\n| HTTP Client | requests |\n| Token Tracking | LiteLLM Proxy (port 4000) |\n| Reporting | matplotlib, rich, HTML generation |\n| Data Validation | Pydantic-style schema validation |\n| Build | Makefile |\n\n**Target Project (AgentCube):**\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python >= 3.10 |\n| HTTP Framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n| Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n| Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n| Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n| Container | Alpine 3.19, Ubuntu 24.04 |\n| Scheduler | Volcano (optional) |\n\n### 4. AgentCube Architecture (Target Project)\n\nAgentCube is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform** for AI agents with these core components:\n\n1. **Router** (Go) -- Ingress component; handles HTTP/gRPC, auth, session routing, connection proxying to data plane\n2. **Workload Manager** (Go) -- Session lifecycle management, warm pool, resource allocation, Redis state\n3. **Controller Manager** (Go) -- Kubernetes controller for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n4. **PicoD** (Go) -- Pod Interception Daemon; runs inside sandbox pods, handles SSH, command execution, file ops\n5. **Agentd** (Go) -- Idle resource detection and cleanup daemon\n6. **Python SDK** -- `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` with context manager support\n7. **Store** -- Redis/Valkey for session state, caching, pub/sub\n\n### 5. Existing Documentation\n\n**Docusaurus Documentation Site** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/docs/`):\n- **Introduction**: index.md, quickstart.md, concepts.md (glossary, session lifecycle, resource management)\n- **Architecture**:\n  - `overview.md` (463 lines) -- System architecture, tech stack, design principles, scalability, Mermaid diagrams\n  - `modules.md` (1412 lines) -- Detailed module docs: Router, Workload Manager, Store, PicoD, Controller Manager, Agentd with Go code examples\n  - `data-flow.md` (715 lines) -- Request flows, session state machine, error handling, warm pool, security flows, distributed tracing\n  - `security.md` (799 lines) -- AuthN/AuthZ, network isolation, RBAC, container security, encryption, auditing, threat model\n  - `observability.md` (807 lines) -- Prometheus metrics, Grafana dashboards, structured logging, distributed tracing, alerting\n\n**Spec-driven Documentation Pattern** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/`):\nEach capability domain has two files:\n- `spec.md` -- Requirements in Given/When/Then format with SHALL/SHOULD/MAY normative language\n- `design.md` -- Implementation design with Go code examples, package structures, file layouts\n\n10 capability domains: sandbox-orchestration, session-routing, code-execution, session-store, idle-cleanup, cli-toolkit, python-sdk, deployment, ci-cd, integrations\n\n### 6. Task Tracking and Planning Patterns\n\n**OpenSpec OPSX Workflow** (8 stages ST-0 through ST-7):\n```\nST-0 AR Input       → changes/{AR-ID}/\nST-1 Clarification   → proposal.md\nST-2 Spec Design     → delta-spec.md\nST-3 Design          → design.md\nST-4 Task Breakdown  → tasks.md\nST-5 Implementation  → code files\nST-6 Verification    → verification report\nST-7 Archive         → spec merge\n```\n\n**Task File Pattern** (e.g., `tasks.md`, `tasks/ar-030-tasks.md`, `changes/AR-026/tasks.md`):\n- Header: Module, Language, Size (S/M/L), Status\n- Tasks grouped by phase (T001, T002, ...)\n- Each task has checkbox items with file paths, logic descriptions, and verification criteria\n- Final \"Verification\" section with cross-cutting checks\n\n**Key Planning Files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md` -- 1441-line implementation plan for AR-023 through AR-033, mapping 78 files across 11 ARs with 4 implementation phases\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/PROPOSAL.md` -- Evaluation methodology, 5-dimension metric system (Stage, Role, Efficiency, Quality, Distribution), token tracking方案\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/configs/config.yaml` -- Full benchmark config: 6 CLI tools, 6+ models, 10 capability domains, 117 requirements, 172 scenarios\n\n### 7. Metric System (5 Dimensions)\n\n| Dimension | Codes | Examples |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Stage | ST-0 ~ ST-7 | Per-stage input/output/cache tokens, iterations, duration |\n| Role | RT-AI, RT-HUMAN, RT-RATIO, RT-ITER | AI tokens, human tokens, human:AI ratio |\n| Efficiency | ET-LOC, ET-FILE, ET-TASK, ET-AR | Token per LOC, per file, per task, per AR |\n| Quality | QT-COV, QT-CONSIST, QT-AVAIL, QT-BUG | Token per coverage%, consistency%, availability%, bug |\n| Distribution | PT-DESIGN, PT-DEV, PT-VERIFY, PT-PEAK | Design/dev/verify phase ratios, peak stage |\n\n### 8. Supported CLI Tools and Models\n\n**CLI Tools**: claude-code, gemini-cli, cursor-cli, opencode-cli\n**Models**: claude-sonnet-4, claude-4.6-opus-high-thinking, gemini-3.1-pro, gemini-2.5-pro, gpt-4.1, glm-5, glm-4.7, kimi-k2.5, minimax-m2.5, qwen3.5-plus, qwen3.6-plus\n\n### 9. Documentation Patterns Summary\n\n1. **Markdown-first**: All documentation is in Markdown\n2. **Frontmatter**: Docusaurus docs use YAML frontmatter (`title`, `sidebar_label`)\n3. **Mermaid diagrams**: Architecture, data flow, and state machine diagrams embedded as Mermaid\n4. **Code examples**: Go and Python code blocks with implementation details\n5. **Tables**: Extensive use of tables for configuration, comparison, and reference data\n6. **Normative language**: Specs use SHALL/SHOULD/MAY terminology\n7. **Given/When/Then**: Scenarios follow BDD-style format\n8. **Checklist tasks**: Task files use `- [ ]` markdown checkboxes with verification criteria\n9. **Cross-references**: Docs use relative links and Docusaurus sidebar navigation\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2841310e9ffejxxkSlMRvtRt1d","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775900618516,"end":1775900728585}}}}
